B_CIRCUIT_ELEMENTS
# Circuit element line format:
#
#  Key to abbreviations used in line format descriptions:
#      name  => element name
#      pnx   => positive node x
#      pny   => positive node y
#      nnx   => negative node x
#      nny   => negative node y
#      pnl   => positive node layer number
#      nnl   => negative node layer number
#      ecx   => element corner x (usually equal to positive node x)
#      ecy   => element corner y (usually equal to negative node y)
#      (P)C  => (parasitic) capacitance value in Farads
#      (P)L  => (parasitic) inductance  value in Henrys
#      (P)R  => (parasitic) resistance  value in Ohms
#      mag   => source magnitude in either Volts or Amperes
#      phase => source phase in degrees
#
#  Capacitor:      CAP    <name> <pnx> <pny> <nnx> <nny> <pnl> <nnl> <ecx> <ecy> <C>   <PL> <PR>
#  Inductor:       IND    <name> <pnx> <pny> <nnx> <nny> <pnl> <nnl> <ecx> <ecy> <PC>  <L>  <PR>
#  Resistor:       RES    <name> <pnx> <pny> <nnx> <nny> <pnl> <nnl> <ecx> <ecy> <PC>  <L>  <PR>
#  Voltage Source: VSRC   <name> <pnx> <pny> <nnx> <nny> <pnl> <nnl> <ecx> <ecy> <mag> <PR> <phase>
#  Current Source: CSRC   <name> <pnx> <pny> <nnx> <nny> <pnl> <nnl> <ecx> <ecy> <mag> <PR> <phase>
#  Port:           PORT   <name> <pnx> <pny> <nnx> <nny> <pnl> <nnl> <ecx> <ecy>
#  Voltage Probe:  VPROBE <name> <pnx> <pny> <nnx> <nny> <pnl> <nnl> <ecx> <ecy>
#
#  Notes: parasitic resistance values for voltage and current sources
#         MUST be non-zero
#         (ecx,ecy) indicates the location of the 90 degree bend in the
#         circuit element's wires (used for display purposes only)
#
